# i18n Enforcement

Every new UI element must respect the active language toggle (`id` | `en`).

## Never hardcode visible UI text

```tsx
// ❌ BAD
<button>Save Draft</button>
<p>No products match your search.</p>

// ✅ GOOD
const { t, tStrict } = useTranslation();
<button>{t("common.saveDraft")}</button>
<p>{tStrict("bbUi.noProductsMatch")}</p>
```

- Use `t()` or `tStrict()` from `useTranslation()`.
- Business Brain UI: prefer `useBbTranslation()` → `bb("key")` (maps to `bbUi.*`).
- Add keys to **both** `id` and `en` dictionaries before shipping.

## Locale rules

| Locale | UI language |
|--------|-------------|
| `id` | Bahasa Indonesia — no English UI labels |
| `en` | English |

Brand terms may stay unchanged: Business Brain, AI, WhatsApp, Desklabs.

## Do NOT translate (user-generated content)

Customer messages, AI replies, product names, article content, document names, company profile text, WhatsApp messages.

System defaults only (e.g. `untitledProduct` → `Produk Tanpa Nama`).

## DO translate (product UI)

Labels, buttons, placeholders, filters, empty states, helper text, status badges, tooltips, tabs, section titles, error messages.

## Missing keys (development guard)

`createStrictTranslator` / `tStrict`:
- Logs `[i18n] Missing translation key: …` in development
- Renders `[key]` in development — never silently falls back to English when locale is `id`

Prefer `tStrict()` for new UI so missing keys surface immediately.

## Adding translations

1. Add key to English dictionary (`lib/i18n/dictionary.ts`, `lib/i18n/bb-ui-dictionary.ts`, etc.)
2. Add matching Indonesian translation
3. Reference via typed key: `t("namespace.key")` or `bb("key")`
